<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,258,1039]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,906,931]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">Notes.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[330,428,906,931]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">holotype</typeStatus>
is part of a series of specimens identified by Baker as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker. Labeled" authorityYear="1914" box="[1036,1134,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[1036,1134,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This is one of four known species in the genus that have the dorsum uniformly black, without red, yellow or white markings. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baker. Labeled" authorityYear="1914" box="[151,248,979,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis box="[151,248,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser, 2019" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser" authorityYear="2019" box="[262,413,979,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranigra" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[262,413,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">M. paranigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[419,482,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[419,482,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser, 2019" authorityName="Dietrich &amp; Zahniser" authorityYear="2019" box="[535,681,979,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[535,681,979,1002]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">M. siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,751,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[688,751,978,1003]" pageId="15" pageNumber="488" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having the lateral processes of the aedeagal atrium slender with bulblike apices.
</paragraph>
